abstract: Sam’s Club, a division of Wal-Mart Stores, will enter the realm of private-label distilled spirits with a vodka named Rue 33.
snippet: Sam’s Club, a division of Wal-Mart Stores, will enter the realm of private-label distilled spirits with a vodka named Rue 33.
lead_paragraph: As the economy continues to worry consumers, lower-priced private-label products are growing in popularity — even in warehouse stores, where the cost of merchandise is typically already lower.

headline.main: Sam’s Club Adds a Private-Label Vodka
